                          <p
                            id="fs-idm198587408"
                          >Using these concentrations, the pH of the solution may be computed as in part (a) above, yielding pH = 4.75 (only slightly different from that prior to adding the strong base).</p>
                          <p id="fs-idm140802864">
                            (c) For comparison, calculate the pH after 1.0 mL of 0.10
                            <em data-effect="italics">M</em> NaOH is added to 100 mL of a solution of an unbuffered solution with a pH of 4.74.
                          </p>
                          <p
                            id="fs-idm216667360"
                          >The amount of hydrogen ion initially present in the solution is</p>
                          <div data-type="equation" id="fs-idm181266816">
                            <math display="block">
                              <semantics>
                                <mrow>
                                  <mrow>
                                    <mo stretchy="false">[</mo>
                                    <msub>
                                      <mtext>H</mtext>
                                      <mn>3</mn>
                                    </msub>
                                    <msup>
                                      <mtext>O</mtext>
                                      <mo>+</mo>
                                    </msup>
                                    <mo stretchy="false">]</mo>
                                    <mo>=</mo>
